subject:

SHOULD BE A CONTINIOUS PART OF LIFE
===================================================================
verse:

David appointed a group of Levites to lead the people in
worship before the Ark of the Lord by asking for His blessings
and giving thanks and praise to the Lord, the God of Israel. 

(I Chron. 16:4)
===================================================================
reflection:

Certain Levities were appointed to give continual praise and
thanks to God. Praise and thanksgiving should be a
regular part of our routine, not reserved only for 
celebrations. If we praise God continually, we will find that 
we will not take God’s blessing for granted.
===================================================================
prayer:

Gracious God,
You are worthy of praise at all times. As the Levites were 
appointed to offer continual thanksgiving, teach my heart to 
echo their devotion. Let my first thoughts in the morning and 
my last thoughts at night be gratitude for Your steadfast 
love and daily mercies.

Guard me from taking Your blessings for granted. Open my eyes 
to the gifts I overlook—breath in my lungs, strength for each 
task, forgiveness through Christ, and the quiet guidance of 
Your Spirit. Turn my routine into worship, my work into 
offering, and my pauses into praise.

When worries crowd my mind, lift my gaze to Your faithfulness. 
When joy overflows, anchor it in grateful remembrance of Your 
goodness. May my life become a living hymn, giving You honor 
in word and deed, today and always.

In Jesus’ name, Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
